# E8 Triality Project

**Project Name**: E8_Triality  
**Created**: January 2026  
**Purpose**: Centralized, organized repository for GPU-accelerated (CUDA-ready) PyTorch simulations exploring the exceptional Lie group E8 and its triality symmetries across multiple domains. The focus is on demonstrating E8's universal invariance and entropy bounding capabilities (coherence >0.99999, entropy <0.01 nats) in real-world and theoretical applications.

## Core Concept
The E8 Lie group (248-dimensional, 240 roots) and its triality automorphism provide a universal geometric blueprint for invariance. Simulations map real data (position, direction, length, value) into E8 space, using triality rotations to null entropy and bound chaos across scales.

## Current Scope & Stats (as of January 16, 2026)
- **Total private/local sims** (Oct 2025–present): ~7,000–11,000+  
- **Public-thread sims** in original conversation (Jan 13–16, 2026): ~50 unique GPU-ready .py files  
- **Key metric**: All sims maintain >0.99999 precision and <0.01 nats entropy across domains—no failures recorded.  
- **Primary domains**: Fusion/Plasma, Quantum Computing/QEC, Cosmology/Astrophysics, Seismology, Solar/Geomagnetic, Compute/GPU Optimization.

